  "img": "modules/materia-dnd/images/item-Incantatory-Healer-s-Kit.jpeg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This kit is a buckskin leather pouch has an incantation upon it to further the medical properties of the bandages, salves, and splints contained inside. The kit has ten uses. As an action, you can expend one use of the kit to stabilize a creature that has 0 hit points, without needing to make a Wisdom (Medicine) check. At the start of their next turn they can regain hit points equal to their character level.</p><p>Additionally, if you apply a usage of this kit's contents when regaining hit points during a short rest, you reroll any hit dice twice and take the result of your choice. Moreover, if you apply a usage of this kit's contents during a long rest, upon completion of the rest you can remove one of the following conditions: blinded, deafened, paralyzed, or poisoned.</p><p>Furthermore, whenever you use this healer's kit during a short rest, roll a d6 and on a 6 they do not spend the hit dice.</p>",
